<Layout title="Mayoral Tracker" description="Where do the candidates for Denver Mayor stand on the issues? Ten questions on executive authority, sent to every candidate.">
  <section class="hero-mini">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 data-en="Mayoral Tracker" data-es="Rastreador de Alcalde">Mayoral Tracker</h1>
      <p data-en="The mayor proposes the budget, runs the police, and signs or vetoes every ordinance. We sent every declared mayoral candidate ten questions about how they'd use that power. Their answers — and silences — are below." data-es="El alcalde propone el presupuesto, dirige la policía y firma o veta cada ordenanza. Enviamos a cada candidato declarado a alcalde diez preguntas sobre cómo usarían ese poder. Sus respuestas — y silencios — están abajo.">
        The mayor proposes the budget, runs the police, and signs or vetoes every ordinance. We sent every declared mayoral candidate ten questions about how they'd use that power. Their answers — and silences — are below.
      </p>
      <p class="hero-sublink" data-en="Looking for City Council races? See the Council Candidate Tracker." data-es="&iquest;Buscas las carreras del Concejo Municipal? Consulta el Rastreador de Candidatos del Concejo.">
        Looking for City Council races? See the <a href="/tools/candidate-tracker">Council Candidate Tracker</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Questionnaire -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2 data-en="The Questions" data-es="Las Preguntas">The Questions</h2>
        <p data-en="Ten questions about executive power. The mayor controls what council cannot: the budget proposal, department leadership, police operations, and veto authority. These questions are designed to put candidates on record about how they'd wield that power." data-es="Diez preguntas sobre el poder ejecutivo. El alcalde controla lo que el concejo no puede: la propuesta de presupuesto, el liderazgo de departamentos, las operaciones policiales y la autoridad de veto. Estas preguntas están diseñadas para que los candidatos se posicionen sobre cómo ejercerían ese poder.">
          Ten questions about executive power. The mayor controls what council cannot: the budget proposal, department leadership, police operations, and veto authority. These questions are designed to put candidates on record about how they'd wield that power.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="questions-list">
        <div class="question-category" data-en="HOUSING & HOMELESSNESS" data-es="VIVIENDA Y PERSONAS SIN HOGAR">HOUSING & HOMELESSNESS</div>

        <div class="question-card">
          <span class="question-number">1</span>
          <div>
            <h3 data-en="Rent Stabilization & Tenant Protection" data-es="Estabilización de Alquileres y Protección de Inquilinos">Rent Stabilization & Tenant Protection</h3>
            <p data-en="Colorado currently preempts cities from enacting rent control. If the state enables it, would you sign a rent stabilization ordinance? What annual cap would you support? If the state does not act, what executive actions would you take to protect tenants — through enforcement of existing habitability codes, just-cause eviction protections, or directing city resources to tenant legal defense?" data-es="Colorado actualmente impide que las ciudades implementen control de alquileres. Si el estado lo permite, ¿firmaría una ordenanza de estabilización de alquileres? ¿Qué tope anual apoyaría? Si el estado no actúa, ¿qué acciones ejecutivas tomaría para proteger a los inquilinos — mediante la aplicación de códigos de habitabilidad existentes, protecciones de desalojo por causa justa, o dirigiendo recursos municipales a la defensa legal de inquilinos?">
              Colorado currently preempts cities from enacting rent control. <strong>If the state enables it, would you sign a rent stabilization ordinance? What annual cap would you support?</strong> If the state does not act, what executive actions would you take to protect tenants — through enforcement of existing habitability codes, just-cause eviction protections, or directing city resources to tenant legal defense?
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="question-card">
          <span class="question-number">2</span>
          <div>
            <h3 data-en="Homelessness & Encampment Policy" data-es="Personas sin Hogar y Política de Campamentos">Homelessness & Encampment Policy</h3>
            <p data-en="Denver City Council passed a moratorium on encampment sweeps during freezing temperatures. Mayor Johnston vetoed it. As mayor, would you sign or veto a freezing-weather moratorium? The Johnston administration's hotel shelter model has housed thousands but critics say it lacks wraparound services and functions as a revolving door. What is your specific plan for reducing unsheltered homelessness — and how would you measure success?" data-es="El Concejo Municipal de Denver aprobó una moratoria sobre desalojos de campamentos durante temperaturas bajo cero. El Alcalde Johnston la vetó. Como alcalde, ¿firmaría o vetaría una moratoria durante clima helado? El modelo de refugios en hoteles de la administración Johnston ha alojado a miles, pero los críticos dicen que carece de servicios integrales y funciona como una puerta giratoria. ¿Cuál es su plan específico para reducir la falta de vivienda sin refugio — y cómo mediría el éxito?">
              Denver City Council passed a moratorium on encampment sweeps during freezing temperatures. Mayor Johnston vetoed it. <strong>As mayor, would you sign or veto a freezing-weather moratorium?</strong> The Johnston administration's hotel shelter model has housed thousands but critics say it lacks wraparound services and functions as a revolving door. What is your specific plan for reducing unsheltered homelessness — and how would you measure success?
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="question-category" data-en="PUBLIC SAFETY & POLICING" data-es="SEGURIDAD PÚBLICA Y POLICÍA">PUBLIC SAFETY & POLICING</div>

        <div class="question-card">
          <span class="question-number">3</span>
          <div>
            <h3 data-en="STAR & LEAD Expansion" data-es="Expansión de STAR y LEAD">STAR & LEAD Expansion</h3>
            <p data-en="Denver's STAR program sends mental health professionals instead of police to crisis calls (10,000+ calls, zero incidents requiring police backup). The LEAD program diverts people facing low-level charges to case management instead of arrest (Seattle evaluation: 58% lower recidivism). Both programs report to the mayor's office. Would you fund expansion to 24/7 citywide coverage in your first budget? Should community members be able to make LEAD referrals directly, without requiring police contact?" data-es="El programa STAR de Denver envía profesionales de salud mental en lugar de policía a llamadas de crisis (más de 10,000 llamadas, cero incidentes que requirieron respaldo policial). El programa LEAD desvía a personas que enfrentan cargos menores a gestión de casos en lugar de arresto (evaluación de Seattle: 58% menor reincidencia). Ambos programas reportan a la oficina del alcalde. ¿Financiaría la expansión a cobertura 24/7 en toda la ciudad en su primer presupuesto? ¿Deberían los miembros de la comunidad poder hacer referencias a LEAD directamente, sin requerir contacto policial?">
              Denver's STAR program sends mental health professionals instead of police to crisis calls (10,000+ calls, zero incidents requiring police backup). The LEAD program diverts people facing low-level charges to case management instead of arrest (Seattle evaluation: 58% lower recidivism). Both programs report to the mayor's office. <strong>Would you fund expansion to 24/7 citywide coverage in your first budget? Should community members be able to make LEAD referrals directly, without requiring police contact?</strong>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="question-card">
          <span class="question-number">4</span>
          <div>
            <h3 data-en="Police Budget & Community Safety" data-es="Presupuesto Policial y Seguridad Comunitaria">Police Budget & Community Safety</h3>
            <p data-en="The mayor proposes the city budget. Denver For All proposes a phased reallocation of the police budget: Phase 1 (~8% / $25M) expands STAR and LEAD citywide; Phase 2 (~15% / $45M) adds violence intervention and substance treatment; Phase 3 (~25% / $75M) adds youth services, restorative justice, and housing. Each phase evaluated before the next begins. Would you propose this reallocation in your budget? If not, what level would you support, and where would you direct the funds?" data-es="El alcalde propone el presupuesto de la ciudad. Denver Para Todos propone una reasignación gradual del presupuesto policial: Fase 1 (~8% / $25M) expande STAR y LEAD a toda la ciudad; Fase 2 (~15% / $45M) agrega intervención de violencia y tratamiento de sustancias; Fase 3 (~25% / $75M) agrega servicios juveniles, justicia restaurativa y vivienda. Cada fase se evalúa antes de comenzar la siguiente. ¿Propondría esta reasignación en su presupuesto? Si no, ¿qué nivel apoyaría y a dónde dirigiría los fondos?">
              The mayor proposes the city budget. Denver For All proposes a phased reallocation of the police budget: Phase 1 (~8% / $25M) expands STAR and LEAD citywide; Phase 2 (~15% / $45M) adds violence intervention and substance treatment; Phase 3 (~25% / $75M) adds youth services, restorative justice, and housing. Each phase evaluated before the next begins. <strong>Would you propose this reallocation in your budget? If not, what level would you support, and where would you direct the funds?</strong>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="question-category" data-en="WORKERS & ECONOMIC JUSTICE" data-es="TRABAJADORES Y JUSTICIA ECONÓMICA">WORKERS & ECONOMIC JUSTICE</div>

        <div class="question-card">
          <span class="question-number">5</span>
          <div>
            <h3 data-en="Living Wage & City Workers" data-es="Salario Digno y Trabajadores Municipales">Living Wage & City Workers</h3>
            <p data-en="Denver's minimum wage is $18.29/hour. A single adult with one child needs $27.35/hour to meet basic expenses (MIT Living Wage Calculator). The Johnston administration laid off hundreds of city workers in 2025, drawing sharp criticism. Do you support raising Denver's minimum wage to $25/hour, indexed to cost of living? Do you support eliminating the tipped worker subminimum wage? Would you commit to restoring the laid-off city positions, and do you support collective bargaining rights for city employees?" data-es="El salario mínimo de Denver es $18.29/hora. Un adulto soltero con un hijo necesita $27.35/hora para cubrir gastos básicos (Calculadora de Salario Digno del MIT). La administración Johnston despidió a cientos de trabajadores municipales en 2025, generando fuertes críticas. ¿Apoya aumentar el salario mínimo de Denver a $25/hora, indexado al costo de vida? ¿Apoya eliminar el salario mínimo reducido para trabajadores que reciben propinas? ¿Se comprometería a restaurar los puestos municipales eliminados, y apoya los derechos de negociación colectiva para empleados de la ciudad?">
              Denver's minimum wage is $18.29/hour. A single adult with one child needs $27.35/hour to meet basic expenses (MIT Living Wage Calculator). The Johnston administration laid off hundreds of city workers in 2025, drawing sharp criticism. <strong>Do you support raising Denver's minimum wage to $25/hour, indexed to cost of living? Do you support eliminating the tipped worker subminimum wage?</strong> Would you commit to restoring the laid-off city positions, and do you support collective bargaining rights for city employees?
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="question-category" data-en="INFRASTRUCTURE & QUALITY OF LIFE" data-es="INFRAESTRUCTURA Y CALIDAD DE VIDA">INFRASTRUCTURE & QUALITY OF LIFE</div>

        <div class="question-card">
          <span class="question-number">6</span>
          <div>
            <h3 data-en="Municipal Broadband" data-es="Banda Ancha Municipal">Municipal Broadband</h3>
            <p data-en="Denver voters approved municipal broadband in 2020, but the city has not built it. The mayor controls DOTI and the departments responsible for implementation. Comcast and CenturyLink charge some of the highest internet prices in the country, and 15% of Denver households lack broadband access. Would you direct city departments to begin building city-owned fiber internet infrastructure? What timeline would you commit to?" data-es="Los votantes de Denver aprobaron la banda ancha municipal en 2020, pero la ciudad no la ha construido. El alcalde controla DOTI y los departamentos responsables de la implementación. Comcast y CenturyLink cobran algunos de los precios de internet más altos del país, y el 15% de los hogares de Denver carecen de acceso a banda ancha. ¿Dirigiría a los departamentos de la ciudad a comenzar a construir infraestructura de internet de fibra óptica propiedad de la ciudad? ¿A qué plazo se comprometería?">
              Denver voters approved municipal broadband in 2020, but the city has not built it. The mayor controls DOTI and the departments responsible for implementation. <strong>Would you direct city departments to begin building city-owned fiber internet infrastructure? What timeline would you commit to?</strong>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="question-card">
          <span class="question-number">7</span>
          <div>
            <h3 data-en="Disability Rights & Inclusion" data-es="Derechos de las Personas con Discapacidad e Inclusión">Disability Rights & Inclusion</h3>
            <p data-en="Over 70,000 Denver residents live with a disability. People with disabilities make up a third to half of all people killed by police nationally. Less than 5% of Denver's housing stock is wheelchair accessible. 40% of Denver's sidewalks fail ADA width standards. The Commission for People with Disabilities is advisory-only — the mayor appoints its members. Would you elevate the Commission from advisory to enforcement authority? Would you direct DOTI to prioritize ADA sidewalk compliance in its construction schedule?" data-es="Más de 70,000 residentes de Denver viven con una discapacidad. Las personas con discapacidad representan de un tercio a la mitad de todas las personas asesinadas por la policía a nivel nacional. Menos del 5% de las viviendas de Denver son accesibles para sillas de ruedas. El 40% de las aceras de Denver no cumplen con los estándares de ancho de la ADA. La Comisión para Personas con Discapacidades es solo consultiva — el alcalde nombra a sus miembros. ¿Elevaría la Comisión de consultiva a autoridad con poder de aplicación? ¿Dirigiría a DOTI a priorizar el cumplimiento de la ADA en aceras en su calendario de construcción?">
              Over 70,000 Denver residents live with a disability. Less than 5% of Denver's housing stock is wheelchair accessible. 40% of Denver's sidewalks fail ADA width standards. The Commission for People with Disabilities is advisory-only — the mayor appoints its members. <strong>Would you elevate the Commission from advisory to enforcement authority? Would you direct DOTI to prioritize ADA sidewalk compliance in its construction schedule?</strong>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="question-category" data-en="DEMOCRACY & ACCOUNTABILITY" data-es="DEMOCRACIA Y RENDICIÓN DE CUENTAS">DEMOCRACY & ACCOUNTABILITY</div>

        <div class="question-card">
          <span class="question-number">8</span>
          <div>
            <h3 data-en="Flock Cameras & Surveillance" data-es="Cámaras Flock y Vigilancia">Flock Cameras & Surveillance</h3>
            <p data-en="Denver City Council voted 12-0 to reject the Flock ALPR camera contract. Mayor Johnston bypassed council by structuring a contract just under the $500K approval threshold. Audit logs revealed ICE searched Denver's camera data 1,400+ times. As mayor, would you terminate the Flock contract? Would you support requiring council approval before any surveillance technology is deployed? Should Denver restrict federal law enforcement access to city surveillance data?" data-es="El Concejo Municipal de Denver votó 12-0 para rechazar el contrato de cámaras ALPR de Flock. El Alcalde Johnston evadió al concejo estructurando un contrato justo por debajo del umbral de aprobación de $500K. Los registros de auditoría revelaron que ICE buscó los datos de las cámaras de Denver más de 1,400 veces. Como alcalde, ¿terminaría el contrato con Flock? ¿Apoyaría requerir la aprobación del concejo antes de implementar cualquier tecnología de vigilancia? ¿Debería Denver restringir el acceso de la policía federal a los datos de vigilancia de la ciudad?">
              Denver City Council voted 12-0 to reject the Flock ALPR camera contract. Mayor Johnston bypassed council by structuring a contract just under the $500K approval threshold. Audit logs revealed ICE searched Denver's camera data 1,400+ times. <strong>As mayor, would you terminate the Flock contract? Would you support requiring council approval before any surveillance technology is deployed?</strong> Should Denver restrict federal law enforcement access to city surveillance data?
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="question-card">
          <span class="question-number">9</span>
          <div>
            <h3 data-en="Participatory Budgeting" data-es="Presupuesto Participativo">Participatory Budgeting</h3>
            <p data-en="The mayor proposes the city's $1.8 billion general fund budget. Cities like Paris, New York, and Porto Alegre let residents directly decide how to spend portions of the public budget. Denver has no participatory budgeting program. Would you allocate a portion of your proposed budget to direct resident control? What dollar amount? How would you structure the process to ensure low-income communities and communities of color have equal voice?" data-es="El alcalde propone el presupuesto del fondo general de $1.8 mil millones de la ciudad. Ciudades como París, Nueva York y Porto Alegre permiten que los residentes decidan directamente cómo gastar porciones del presupuesto público. Denver no tiene un programa de presupuesto participativo. ¿Asignaría una porción de su presupuesto propuesto al control directo de los residentes? ¿Qué cantidad en dólares? ¿Cómo estructuraría el proceso para asegurar que las comunidades de bajos ingresos y las comunidades de color tengan voz igualitaria?">
              The mayor proposes the city's $1.8 billion general fund budget. Cities like Paris, New York, and Porto Alegre let residents directly decide how to spend portions of the public budget. Denver has no participatory budgeting program. <strong>Would you allocate a portion of your proposed budget to direct resident control? What dollar amount?</strong> How would you structure the process to ensure low-income communities and communities of color have equal voice?
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="question-category" data-en="OPEN-ENDED" data-es="PREGUNTA ABIERTA">OPEN-ENDED</div>

        <div class="question-card">
          <span class="question-number">10</span>
          <div>
            <h3 data-en="Denver's Top Priority" data-es="La Prioridad Principal de Denver">Denver's Top Priority</h3>
            <p data-en="What is the single most important issue facing Denver, and what specific policy would you implement in your first year as mayor to address it? Be specific: name the problem, name the solution, name how you'd pay for it." data-es="&iquest;Cu&aacute;l es el problema m&aacute;s importante que enfrenta Denver y qu&eacute; pol&iacute;tica espec&iacute;fica implementar&iacute;a en su primer a&ntilde;o como alcalde para abordarlo? Sea espec&iacute;fico: nombre el problema, nombre la soluci&oacute;n, nombre c&oacute;mo lo financiar&iacute;a.">
              <strong>What is the single most important issue facing Denver, and what specific policy would you implement in your first year as mayor to address it?</strong> Be specific: name the problem, name the solution, name how you'd pay for it.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Mayor's Race -->
